# GitHub workflow

## Branches

- `git pull` on `main` before starting work.
- Branch names: `feat/short-description`, `fix/...`, `chore/...`.
- Never force-push to `main`.

## Changes ship via PR

- Push branch → `gh pr create` (or GitHub UI).
- Wait for CI (Actions tab) before merge.
- Do not merge blind reruns — read failed job logs first.
- Agent does not push to `main` unless the user explicitly asks.

## Commits

- Format: `type(scope): what and why` (e.g. `fix(combat): cap despawn batch`).
- Never commit: `.env`, keys, `*credentials*`, large binary dumps.

## Sensitive paths

- Respect `CODEOWNERS` when present.
- Production secrets live in GitHub Environments (admins only).

## CLI

Use `gh` for PRs, checks, issues — always approved for this account (`pfaustino`).
